summary: An Ordinance amending Section 3 of Ordinance No. 26825, entitled "An Ordinance granting to W. H. Coughlin, his successors and assigns, a franchise to construct, maintain and operate a street railway upon certain parts of West Michigan Street, and other streets, avenues and places in the City of Seattle," approved March 27, 1911 for the purpose of granting an extensions of time in which to begin construction as required by said franchise ordinance.
